Pre-processing workflow


BCCIO <- NormalizeData(BCCIO, normalization.method= "LogNormalize", scale.factor = 10000) # Normalize feature expression 

BCCIO <- FindVariableFeatures(BCCIO, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 2000) # Feature selection (highly variable features)

all.genes <- rownames(BCCIO)
BCCIO <- ScaleData(BCCIO, features = all.genes) # Scale data in preparation for PCA 
BCCIO <- RunPCA(BCCIO, features = VariableFeatures(object = BCCIO)) # Perform PCA

Create a dumbbell plot comparing the differential expression of genes between responders and nonresponders, pretreatment vs. posttreatment (Regulatory T cells)



BCC.pre.Tregs.data <- BCC.pre.Tregs$data %>% select(GeneNames, xvals, yvals)
BCC.post.Tregs.data <- BCC.post.Tregs$data %>% select(GeneNames, xvals, yvals)

BCC.pre.Tregs.data <- filter(BCC.pre.Tregs.data, xvals < -0.5 | xvals > 0.5, yvals < 0.05)
BCC.post.Tregs.data <- filter(BCC.post.Tregs.data, xvals < -0.5 | xvals > 0.5, yvals < 0.05)

BCC.pre.Tregs.data$xvals[BCC.pre.Tregs.data$xvals < -2] <- -2
BCC.pre.Tregs.data$xvals[BCC.pre.Tregs.data$xvals > 2] <- 2

BCC.post.Tregs.data$xvals[BCC.post.Tregs.data$xvals < -2] <- -2
BCC.post.Tregs.data$xvals[BCC.post.Tregs.data$xvals > 2] <- 2

BCC.pre.Tregs.data$Treatment <- "Pre-treatment"
BCC.post.Tregs.data$Treatment <- "Post-treatment"

BCC.Tregs.data <- rbind(BCC.pre.Tregs.data, BCC.post.Tregs.data)
BCC.Tregs.data <- BCC.Tregs.data %>% group_by(GeneNames) %>% filter(n()>1)

BCC.Tregs.data <- BCC.Tregs.data[order(BCC.Tregs.data$GeneNames),]
BCC.Tregs.data$paired <- 0
for (i in 1:nrow(BCC.Tregs.data)) {
  BCC.Tregs.data$paired[i] <- ceiling(i/2)
}

BCC.Tregs.data$yvals <- -log10(BCC.Tregs.data$yvals)

BCC.Tregs.data %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = xvals, y = GeneNames)) +
  labs(title = "Regulatory T cells",
       x = expression("Log"[2]*" Fold Change"),
       y = "Gene") +
  geom_line(aes(group = paired), color="black", size=1) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = Treatment, size = yvals)) +
  guides(size = FALSE) +
  theme_light() +
  theme(legend.position="top", 
        plot.title = element_text(color="black", size=24, face="bold", hjust = 0.5)) +
  xlim(-2,2)

Dumbbell charts for every cell type


celltypes <- c("CD8_activation", "CD8_exhausted", "CD8_memory", "CD4", "Tregs", "T_proliferation", "Macrophages", "B cells", "NK")

celltypesnames <- c("Activated CD8+ T Cells", "Exhausted CD8+ T Cells", "Memory T Cells", "CD4+ T Cells", "Regulatory T cells", "Proliferating T Cells", "Macrophages", "B Cells", "Natural Killer Cells")

df_pre <- list(BCC.pre.CD8_activation, BCC.pre.CD8_exhausted, BCC.pre.CD8_memory, BCC.pre.CD4, BCC.pre.Tregs, BCC.pre.T_proliferation, BCC.pre.Macrophages, `BCC.pre.B cells`, BCC.pre.NK)

df_post <- list(BCC.post.CD8_activation, BCC.post.CD8_exhausted, BCC.post.CD8_memory, BCC.post.CD4, BCC.post.Tregs, BCC.post.T_proliferation, BCC.post.Macrophages, `BCC.post.B cells`, BCC.post.NK)

for (i in 1:length(celltypes)) {
  assign(paste0("dumbbell.", celltypes[i]), BCC_diffexp_dumbbell(df_pre[[i]], df_post[[i]], 0, 0.05, celltypesnames[i]))
}

dumbbell.malignant <- BCC_diffexp_dumbbell(BCC.pre.malignant, BCC.post.malignant, 0, 0.05, "Malignant Cells")
